# Nicaraguan Banking System Indicators (NBSI): 

## Project Overview

Nicaragua is a small, open economy in Central America, with a GDP per capita of US $2,864.7 in 2024. Its banking sector remains shallow—its gross loan portfolio represents just 31.9 percent of GDP—yet it ranks among the most profitable in the region. In this project, I present a comprehensive analysis of Nicaragua’s banking indicators using publicly available data from the "Superintendencia de Bancos y Otras Instituciones Financieras (SIBOIF)". 

This project provides tools and analysis for:

- Downloading and processing banking system data from SIBOIF.
- Downloading exchange rate information from Central Bank of Nicaragua to convert the metricks
- Creating the following visualizations using tableau:
    - [Statement of Financial Position](https://public.tableau.com/app/profile/christian.bejarano5490/viz/StatementofFinancialPosition/Dashboard)
    - [Income Statement](https://public.tableau.com/app/profile/christian.bejarano5490/viz/IncomeStatement_17496622854550/Dashboard1)

